<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1045,2004]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Wings (
<figureCitation box="[290,402,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1734,1758]" captionTargetBox="[206,1380,271,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[206,1381,271,1710]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Liosphex atratus sp. nov. Ƥ (indicating points of measurements). 1: head in dorsal view; 2: head in frontal view. Liosphex boreus sp. nov. Ƥ. 3: forewing; 4: hindwing; 5 details of forewing; 6: details of forewing. Liosphex trichopleurum Ƥ. 7: shape of m-cu. Abbreviations. cl: clypeus, e: eye, H 1 Rs: height of 1 Rs, IOD: distance between lateral ocelli, lb: labrum, LID: lower interorbital distance, LOD: diameter of lateral ocellus, L 1 Rs: length of 1 Rs, mb: mandible, MOD: diameter of median ocellus, OOD: ocular-ocellar distance, sp: subantennal plate, t: torulus, UID: upper interorbital distance." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/193732/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs 
<number box="[352,402,1904,1930]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
</figureCitation>
): Maximum length of forewing: 
<quantity box="[802,894,1904,1930]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="5.7">5.7 mm</quantity>
[
<quantity box="[910,1064,1904,1930]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" metricValueMax="6.6" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="6.05" valueMax="6.6" valueMin="5.5">5.5–6.6 mm</quantity>
], 
<number box="[1085,1139,1904,1930]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.15">2.15</number>
× [
<number box="[1171,1283,1904,1930]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.275" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.15">2.15–2.4</number>
×] as long as mesosoma. Forewing 
<number box="[412,421,1941,1967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
cu-a distad by M by 2.0× [
<number box="[741,777,1941,1967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.3">1.3</number>
–2.0×] its length. M-cu distinctly curved. 
<number box="[1277,1287,1941,1967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
Rs 
<number box="[1331,1420,1941,1967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.8">1.8–2.2</number>
× as long as high, its basal angle almost rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[747,833,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="8.[151,276,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[206,1380,381,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1381,381,1820]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Liosphex trichopleurum Ƥ. 8: forewing cell 1 Rs; 13: mesosoma in lateral view (showing the distribution of setae). Liosphex atratus sp. nov. Ƥ. 9: forewing cell 1 Rs; 11 &amp; 12: mesosoma in lateral view; general morphology (11) and showing the distribution of setae (12). Liosphex varius Ƥ. 10: forewing cell 1 Rs. Abbreviations: al: anal lobe, bh: basal hamuli, ep: endophragmal pit, es: epistrnal scrobe, hpl: humural plate, jl: jugal lobe, msc: mesoscutum, mn: metanotum, msl: mesosternal lobe, msm: mesepimeron, mss: mesepisternum, mtm: metepimeron, mts: metepisternum, pn: pronotum, prl: pronotal lobe, ps: parapsidal sulcus, sp: spiracle, st: streptaulus, tg: tegula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/193733/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[802,833,1978,2004]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
, in most specimens it is 
<number box="[1120,1154,1978,2004]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="90.0">90</number>
°).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,152,290]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Legs: Forebasitarsus short, its antennal cleaner 
<number box="[770,809,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="0.4">0.4</number>
× its length. Hindtibia with two bristles on only one side of inseration of shorter apical spur (
<figureCitation box="[624,712,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,272,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[206,1380,194,1558]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[206,1381,194,1558]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 25. Liosphex trichopleurum Ƥ. 14: forebasitarsus. Liosphex atratus sp. nov. Ƥ. 15: forebasitarsus; 21: apex of hindtibia in lateral view; 24: tergite III. Liosphex bribri sp. nov. Ƥ. 16: head in frontal view; 19: pronotum in dorsal view. Liosphex guarani sp. nov. Ƥ. 17: head in frontal view; 23: apex of hindtibia in lateral view. Liosphex longicornis sp. nov. Ƥ. 18: head in frontal view. Liosphex maleku sp. nov. Ƥ. 20: pronotum in dorsal view. Liosphex boreus sp. nov. Ƥ. 22: apex of hindtibia in lateral view; 25: tergite III. Abbreviations: bt: basitarsus, ht: hindtibia, its: inseration of tibialspur, Lac: Length of antennal cleaner, Lbt: Length of forebasitarsomere." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/193734/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[679,712,189,215]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,152,290]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Metasoma: Tergite I 
<number box="[446,483,226,252]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.5">1.5</number>
× [
<number box="[515,625,226,252]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.625" valueMax="1.75" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.75</number>
×] as long as wide. At least Tergite III or IV posteromedially with a longitudinal polished and asetose area (
